<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=brikat2005&buddyTimeStamp=20051129&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fprocess_buddy.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059777&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Molly</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Molly lives at <a href='/home/?user=brikat2005'>20936 Eagle Circle</a> in one of Westridge's most spacious and beautiful homes.  She moved to Millsberry on March 12, 2005, and has been enjoying the comfort of living here ever since!<br><br>In addition to being one of the brightest students in her class at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/">Millsberry Academy</a>, Molly is also one of the most athletic.  Ever since her recent discovery of the new <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=360">hockey rink</a> at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a>, Molly has been lacing up her skates and slapping the puck across the ice every afternoon.  Molly also enjoys playing basketball when the weather is bad.  Her specialties include being a tough defender, an aggressive rebounder, and having a knack for blocking the opposing team's shots.  During spring and summertime, Molly can usually be found on the soccer field, expertly dribbling the ball toward her opponent's goal with amazing speed.  When she's not playing soccer, Molly loves to watch the game.  More often than not, she'll be the one wearing a blue and green jersey, while shouting encouragement to her team.<br><br>To keep in good shape for playing sports, Molly exercises very often.  She likes going for long jogs through the hills around Millsberry or swimming laps in a pool.  While exercising, Molly enjoys listening to her favorite pop, punk, and funk songs.  She says that their upbeat rhythms help to keep her energized during workouts.  Since she likes her high-energy mixes so much, Molly recently decided to visit the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a> to produce her very own workout music.  Other citizens have since caught on to Molly's fast-paced songs, and one of her tracks has even entered the top of the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart!<br><br>When Molly wants to relax, she usually heads to the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/theater.phtml">movies</a> with her friends and checks out one of the theater's newest releases.  Molly also finds spending time with animals very relaxing.  Because she is so compassionate, Molly dedicates a lot of her after-school and weekend hours to either working with the frightened animals at an animal shelter, giving Mr. and Mrs. Ruiz a hand at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=9">The Pet Palace</a>, or even practicing obedience-training with puppies in her own backyard.<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Molly, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
